89 static inline int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_configEdma
90 (
91  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj,
92  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg
93 )
94 {
95  int32_t retVal = EDMA_NO_ERROR;
96  uint16_t sampleLenInBytes = sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
97  uint16_t sizeOfDetMatrixElement = sizeof(uint16_t);
98  DPEDMA_syncACfg syncACfg;
99  DPEDMA_syncABCfg syncABCfg;
100  cmplx16ImRe_t *radarCubeBase;
101 
102  if(obj == NULL)
103  {
104  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
105  goto exit;
106  }
107 
108  radarCubeBase = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)obj->cfg.hwRes.radarCube.data;
109 
110  /******************************************************************************************
111  * PROGRAM DMA channel to transfer data from Radar cube to input buffer (ping)
112  ******************************************************************************************/
113  syncABCfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[0]);
114  syncABCfg.destAddress = (uint32_t)(&obj->cfg.hwRes.pingPongBuf[0]);
115  syncABCfg.aCount = sampleLenInBytes;
116  syncABCfg.bCount = cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps;
117  syncABCfg.cCount = 1;/*data for one virtual antenna transferred at a time*/
118  syncABCfg.srcBIdx = cfg->staticCfg.numRxAntennas * cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins * sampleLenInBytes;
119  syncABCfg.dstBIdx = sampleLenInBytes;
120  syncABCfg.srcCIdx = 0U;
121  syncABCfg.dstCIdx = 0U;
122 
123  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncAB(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle,
124  &cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.ping,
125  NULL,//chainingCfg: No chaining
126  &syncABCfg,
127  false,//isEventTriggered
128  true, //isIntermediateTransferCompletionEnabled
129  true,//isTransferCompletionEnabled
130  NULL, //transferCompletionCallbackFxn
131  NULL);//transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg
132 
133  if (retVal != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
134  {
135  goto exit;
136  }
137 
138  /******************************************************************************************
139  * PROGRAM DMA channel to transfer data from Radar cube to input buffer (pong)
140  ******************************************************************************************/
141 
142  /* Transfer parameters are the same as ping, except for src/dst addresses */
143 
144  /*Ping/Pong srcAddress is reprogrammed in every iteration (except for first ping), therefore
145  this srcAddress below will be reprogrammed during processing. In order to avoid recomputing here
146  the first pong srcAddress, it will be hardcoded to a valid address (dummy).*/
147  syncABCfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[0]);/*dummy*/
148  syncABCfg.destAddress = (uint32_t)(&obj->cfg.hwRes.pingPongBuf[cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps]);
149 
150  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncAB(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle,
151  &cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.pong,
152  NULL,//chainingCfg: No chaining
153  &syncABCfg,
154  false,//isEventTriggered
155  true, //isIntermediateTransferCompletionEnabled
156  true,//isTransferCompletionEnabled
157  NULL, //transferCompletionCallbackFxn
158  NULL);//transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg
159

162  goto exit;
163  }
164

210 static inline int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_waitInData(DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj, uint32_t pingPongId)
211 {
212  /* wait until transfer done */
213  volatile bool isTransferDone;
214  uint8_t chId;
215  int32_t retVal = 0;
216 
217  if(pingPongId == DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_PING_IDX)
218  {
219  chId = obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.ping.channel;
220  }
221  else
222  {
223  chId = obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.pong.channel;
224  }
225  do
226  {
227  retVal = EDMA_isTransferComplete(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle,
228  chId,
229  (bool *)&isTransferDone);
230  if(retVal != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
231  {
232  return retVal;
233  }
234  } while (isTransferDone == false);
235 
236  return 0;
237 }

278 /*!************************************************************************************************
279  * @brief DPU_DopplerProcDSP_mult16x32cplx
280  * \par
281  * <b>Description</b> : Multiply a 16-bit complex to a 32-bit complex symbol.
282  *
283  * @param[in] xIQ : 16-bit complex value(16I|16Q packed in 32bits). ImRe format.
284  * @param[in] wQI : 32-bit complex value(32Q|32I packed in 64bits). ReIm format.
285  * @param[out] yQI : pointer to store output 32-bit complex value(32Q|32I). ReIm format.
286  *
287  * @return void
288  **************************************************************************************************
289  */
290 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_mult16x32cplx(uint32_t xIQ, int64_t wQI, int64_t *yQI)
291 {
292  int64_t lltempa, lltempb;
293  int32_t wI, wQ, yI, yQ;
294 
295  wI = (int32_t) _loll(wQI);
296  wQ = (int32_t) _hill(wQI);
297  lltempa = _mpy2ir(xIQ, wI);
298  lltempb = _mpy2ir(xIQ, wQ);
299  yI = _ssub((int32_t)_hill(lltempa), (int32_t)_loll(lltempb));
300  yQ = _sadd((int32_t)_hill(lltempb), (int32_t)_loll(lltempa));
301  *yQI = _itoll(yQ, yI);
302 }

304 /*!************************************************************************************************
305  * @brief DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensationGetCoeff
306  * \par
307  * <b>Description</b> : Get compensation coefficient for Doppler compensation,
308  * by reading the phase shift from the table using half of the
309  * object Doppler index value. If the Doppler index is odd,
310  * an extra half of the bin phase shift is added.
311  *
312  * @param[in] dopplerIdx : Doppler index of the object
313  * @param[in] numDopplerBins : Number of Doppler bins
314  * @param[in] dftSinCosTable : Table with cos/sin values exp(1j*2*pi*k/N)
315  * SIN in even position, COS in odd position,
316  * for k=0,...,N-1 where N is number of Doppler bins.
317  * @param[in] dftHalfBin : exp(1j*2*pi* 0.5 /N) (ImRe format)
318  * @param[out] coeff : Pointer to store the compensation coefficient(ImRe format)
319  *
320  * @return void
321  **************************************************************************************************
322  */
323 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensationGetCoeff
324 (
325  uint16_t dopplerIdx,
326  uint16_t numDopplerBins,
327  uint32_t *dftSinCosTable,
328  uint32_t *dftHalfBin,
329  uint32_t *coeff)
330 {
331  uint32_t expDoppComp;
332  int32_t dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerIdx;
333 
334  /*Divide Doppler index by 2*/
335  if (dopplerCompensationIdx >= numDopplerBins/2)
336  {
337  dopplerCompensationIdx -= numDopplerBins;
338  }
339  dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerCompensationIdx >> 1;
340  if (dopplerCompensationIdx < 0)
341  {
342  dopplerCompensationIdx += numDopplerBins;
343  }
344  expDoppComp = dftSinCosTable[dopplerCompensationIdx];
345  /* Add half bin rotation if Doppler index was odd */
346  if (dopplerIdx & 0x1)
347  {
348  expDoppComp = _cmpyr1(expDoppComp, *dftHalfBin);
349  }
350  *coeff = expDoppComp;
351 }

353 /*!************************************************************************************************
354  * @brief Static inlined function DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensateSingleValue
355  * \par
356  * <b>Description</b> : Compensation of Doppler phase shift in one symbol.
357  * The phase shift read from the table using half of the
358  * object Doppler index value. If the Doppler index is odd,
359  * an extra half of the bin phase shift is added.
360  * Compensation coefficient(16I|16Q) is multiplied to all symbols.
361  *
362  * @param[in] dopplerIdx : Doppler index of the object
363  * @param[in] numDopplerBins : Number of Doppler bins
364  * @param[in] dftSinCosTable : Table with cos/sin values exp(1j*2*pi*k/N)
365  * SIN in even position, COS in odd position, (ImRe format)
366  * for k=0,...,N-1 where N is number of Doppler bins.
367  * @param[in] dftHalfBin : exp(1j*2*pi* 0.5 /N), ImRe format.
368  * @param[in,out] symbolPtr : Pointer to symbol to be Doppler compensated
369  * (32Q|32I each) must be 64 bit aligned. ReIm format.
370  *
371  * @return void
372 
373  **************************************************************************************************
374  */
375 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensateSingleValue(uint16_t dopplerIdx,
376  uint16_t numDopplerBins,
377  uint32_t *dftSinCosTable,
378  uint32_t *dftHalfBin,
379  int64_t * symbolPtr)
380 {
381  uint32_t doppCompCoeff;
382 
383  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensationGetCoeff(dopplerIdx,
384  numDopplerBins,
385  dftSinCosTable,
386  dftHalfBin,
387  &doppCompCoeff);
388 
389  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_mult16x32cplx(doppCompCoeff, symbolPtr[0], symbolPtr );
390 }

409 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_log2AbsAccum
410 (
411  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj,
412  uint16_t rxAntIdx,
413  uint16_t txAntIdx,
414  uint16_t rangeIdx,
415  uint32_t *waitingTime,
416  uint16_t fftOutIndx
417 )
418 {
419  volatile uint32_t startTimeWait;
420  uint32_t idx;
421  uint16_t *log2AbsBuf = (uint16_t *)obj->cfg.hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf;
422 
423  mmwavelib_log2Abs32(
424  (int32_t *) &obj->cfg.hwRes.fftOutBuf[fftOutIndx],
425  log2AbsBuf,
426  obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerBins);
427 
428  /* Check if this is the first virtual antenna for this range bin*/
429  if ((rxAntIdx == 0) && (txAntIdx == 0))
430  {
431  /*This is the first virtual antenna. Starting a new sum. */
432  if (rangeIdx > 0)
433  {
434  /* check if previous sumAbsBuf has been transferred */
435  startTimeWait = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
436  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_waitTransDetMatrix (obj);
437  waitingTime += Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTimeWait;
438  }
439 
440  /* Start new sum*/
441  for (idx = 0; idx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerBins; idx++)
442  {
443  obj->cfg.hwRes.sumAbsBuf[idx] = log2AbsBuf[idx] >> obj->log2VirtAnt;
444  }
445  }
446  else
447  {
448  /*Not the first virtual antenna. Accumulate.*/
449  mmwavelib_accum16shift(log2AbsBuf,
450  obj->cfg.hwRes.sumAbsBuf,
451  obj->log2VirtAnt,
452  obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerBins);
453  }
454 }

469 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_generateTables
470 (
471  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj,
472  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg
473 )
474 {
475  uint32_t tblIdx;
476 
477  /* Generate twiddle factors for Doppler FFT. This is in ReIm format.*/
478  mmwavelib_gen_twiddle_smallfft_32x32((int32_t *)cfg->hwRes.twiddle32x32,
479  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins);
480 
481  /* Generate SIN/COS table for single point DFT */
482  mmwavelib_dftSinCosTabelGen(cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins,
483  (uint32_t *)cfg->hwRes.dftSinCosTable);
484 
485  /* Table starts from DFT size = 4*/
486  tblIdx = 28 - _norm(cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins);
487  obj->dftHalfBin.imag = mmwavelib_dftHalfBinExpValue[tblIdx << 1];
488  obj->dftHalfBin.real = mmwavelib_dftHalfBinExpValue[(tblIdx << 1) + 1];
489 }

504 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_decode2TxBPM
505 (
506  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj,
507  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg
508 )
509 {
510  cmplx32ReIm_t *bpmAPtr;
511  cmplx32ReIm_t *bpmBPtr;
512  int32_t real, imag;
513  uint16_t idx;
514 
515  /*We now have Ping and Pong available.
516  First do doppler compensation on Pong samples.
517  Then do BPM decoding in place:
518  A=S1+S2 (PING)
519  B=S1-S2 (PONG)
520  Compute S1=(A+B)/2 and overwrite A with this value
521  Compute S2=(A-B)/2 and overwrite B with this value
522  A is located in fftOutBuf positions = [0..(numDopplerBins-1)]
523  B is located in fftOutBuf positions = [numDopplerBins..(2*numDopplerBins)]
524  */
525  bpmAPtr = &cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf[0];
526  bpmBPtr = &cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf[cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins];
527  for(idx = 0; idx < cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins; idx++)
528  {
529  /*doppler compensation on Pong*/
530  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_compensateSingleValue(idx,
531  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins,
532  (uint32_t *) cfg->hwRes.dftSinCosTable,
533  (uint32_t *) &obj->dftHalfBin,
534  (int64_t *) &bpmBPtr[idx]);
535 
536  /*decode BPM*/
537  /*first make a copy of A*/
538  real = bpmAPtr[idx].real;
539  imag = bpmAPtr[idx].imag;
540  /*compute S1 and store in A*/
541  bpmAPtr[idx].real = (bpmAPtr[idx].real + bpmBPtr[idx].real)/2;
542  bpmAPtr[idx].imag = (bpmAPtr[idx].imag + bpmBPtr[idx].imag)/2;
543  /*compute S2 and store in B*/
544  bpmBPtr[idx].real = (real - bpmBPtr[idx].real)/2;
545  bpmBPtr[idx].imag = (imag - bpmBPtr[idx].imag)/2;
546  }
547 }

561 static inline void DPU_DopplerProcDSP_clutterRemoval
562 (
563  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg,
564  cmplx16ImRe_t *inputBuf
565 )
566 {
567  uint32_t sumVal[2]={0};
568  cmplx32ImRe_t *pSumVal = (cmplx32ImRe_t *) sumVal;
569  uint32_t meanVal = 0;
570  cmplx16ImRe_t *pMeanVal = (cmplx16ImRe_t *) &meanVal;
571 
572  /*Mmwavelib API requires size to be multiple of 4, which is fine because DPU allows
573  only numDopplerChirps that is multiple of 4*/
574  mmwavelib_vecsum((int16_t *) inputBuf,
575  (int32_t *) sumVal,
576  (int32_t) cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps);
577 
578  /*Divide by numDopplerChirps as the scratch buffer was padded to zero to make it a
579  multiple of 4 so it does not affect the average*/
580  pMeanVal->real = pSumVal->real / cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps ;
581  pMeanVal->imag = pSumVal->imag / cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps ;
582 
583  /*Lib requires size to be multiple of 4*/
584  mmwavelib_vecsubc((int16_t *) inputBuf,
585  (int16_t *) inputBuf,
586  (uint32_t) meanVal,
587  (int32_t) cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps);
588 }

648 int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_config
649 (
650  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Handle handle,
651  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg
652 )
653 {
654  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj;
655  int32_t retVal = 0;
656 
657  obj = (DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *)handle;
658  if(obj == NULL)
659  {
660  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
661  goto exit;
662  }
663 
664  /* Validate params */
665  if(!cfg ||
666  !cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle ||
667  !cfg->hwRes.radarCube.data ||
668  !cfg->hwRes.detMatrix.data ||
669  !cfg->hwRes.pingPongBuf ||
670  !cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf ||
671  !cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf ||
672  !cfg->hwRes.sumAbsBuf ||
673  !cfg->hwRes.dftSinCosTable ||
674  !cfg->hwRes.twiddle32x32 ||
675  !cfg->hwRes.windowCoeff
676  )
677  {
678  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
679  goto exit;
680  }
681 
682  if(obj->inProgress == true)
683  {
684  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
685  goto exit;
686  }
687 
688  /* Check if radar cube format is supported by DPU*/
689  if(cfg->hwRes.radarCube.datafmt != DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_1)
690  {
691  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ECUBEFORMAT;
692  goto exit;
693  }
694 
695  /* Check if detection matrix format is supported by DPU*/
696  if(cfg->hwRes.detMatrix.datafmt != DPIF_DETMATRIX_FORMAT_1)
697  {
698  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EDETMFORMAT;
699  goto exit;
700  }
701 
702  /* Check if number of doppler chirps is a multiple of 4*/
703  if((cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps & 3) != 0)
704  {
705  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ENUMDOPCHIRPS;
706  goto exit;
707  }
708 
709  /* Check if number of doppler bins is at least 16 (due to DSPLIB which requires size of FFT to be
710  at least 16*/
711  if(cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins < 16)
712  {
713  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ENUMDOPBINS;
714  goto exit;
715  }
716 
717  /* Check if DPU configuration is compatible with EDMA max jump size of (32K - 1)*/
718  if(cfg->staticCfg.numRxAntennas * cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) >= 32768)
719  {
720  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EEXCEEDMAXEDMA;
721  goto exit;
722  }
723 
724  /* Check if buffers provided by application have the correct alignment*/
725  if (MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.pingPongBuf , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
726  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf, DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
727  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
728  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.sumAbsBuf , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
729  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.dftSinCosTable , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
730  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.twiddle32x32 , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT)||
731  MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.windowCoeff , DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_BUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT))
732  {
733  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EBUFALIGNMENT;
734  goto exit;
735  }
736 
737  /* Check if detection matrix size is sufficient*/
738  if(cfg->hwRes.detMatrix.dataSize < (cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins *
739  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t)))
740  {
741  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EDETMSIZE;
742  goto exit;
743  }
744 
745  /* Check window Size */
746  if (cfg->hwRes.windowSize != cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps * sizeof(int32_t) / 2U)
747  {
748  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EWINDSIZE;
749  goto exit;
750  }
751 
752  /* check sizes for the scratch buffers provided by application */
753  if((cfg->hwRes.pingPongSize < 2 * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps ) ||
754  (cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsSize < sizeof(cmplx32ReIm_t) * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins ) ||
755  (cfg->hwRes.sumAbsSize < cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t) ) ||
756  (cfg->hwRes.dftSinCosSize < cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) ) ||
757  (cfg->hwRes.twiddleSize < sizeof(cmplx32ReIm_t) * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins ))
758  {
759  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ESCRATCHSIZE;
760  goto exit;
761  }
762 
763  if(cfg->staticCfg.isBpmEnabled)
764  {
765  /* Check if TX antenna configuration is supported for BPM scheme.
766  The only supported scheme for BPM uses both Azimuth TX antennas and no elevation TX antenna*/
767  if(cfg->staticCfg.numTxAntennas != 2)
768  {
769  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EBPMCFG;
770  goto exit;
771  }
772 
773  /* Check if scratch buffer size is enough for BPM decoding*/
774  if(cfg->hwRes.fftOutSize < 2 * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins * sizeof(cmplx32ReIm_t))
775  {
776  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ESCRATCHSIZE;
777  goto exit;
778  }
779  }
780  else
781  {
782  if(cfg->hwRes.fftOutSize < cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins * sizeof(cmplx32ReIm_t))
783  {
784  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ESCRATCHSIZE;
785  goto exit;
786  }
787  }
788 
789  /* Generate tables */
790  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_generateTables(obj, cfg);
791 
792  /* Compute Log2 of numVirtualAntennas */
793  obj->log2VirtAnt = (uint8_t) mathUtils_ceilLog2(cfg->staticCfg.numVirtualAntennas);
794 
795  /* Save necessary parameters to DPU object that will be used during Process time */
796  memcpy((void *)&obj->cfg, (void *)cfg, sizeof(DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config));
797 
798  /* Configure EDMA */
799  retVal = DPU_DopplerProcDSP_configEdma(obj, cfg);
800  if (retVal != 0)
801  {
802  goto exit;
803  }
804 
805  obj->inProgress = false;
806 
807 exit:
808  return retVal;
809 }
810 
825 int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_process
826 (
827  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Handle handle,
828  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_OutParams *outParams
829 )
830 {
831  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj;
832  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Config *cfg;
833  uint16_t rxAntIdx, rangeIdx, txAntIdx;
834  uint16_t nextTransferRxIdx, nextTransferRangeIdx, nextTransferTxIdx;
835  uint16_t rxAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer, txAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer;
836  uint32_t nextTransferIdx, waitingTime, pingPongIdx;
837  volatile uint32_t startTime;
838  volatile uint32_t startTimeWait;
839  int32_t *fftOutPtr;
840  int32_t retVal;
841  uint8_t channel;
842  cmplx16ImRe_t *inpDoppFftBuf;
843  cmplx16ImRe_t *radarCubeBase;
844  cmplx32ReIm_t *windowingOutBuf;
845 
846  retVal = 0;
847  waitingTime = 0;
848  obj = (DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *)handle;
849 
850  if (obj == NULL)
851  {
852  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
853  goto exit;
854  }
855 
856  if(obj->inProgress == true)
857  {
858  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
859  goto exit;
860  }
861  else
862  {
863  obj->inProgress = true;
864  }
865 
866  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
867 
868  radarCubeBase = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)obj->cfg.hwRes.radarCube.data;
869  cfg = &obj->cfg;
870 
871  pingPongIdx = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_PING_IDX;
872 
873  /* trigger first DMA */
874  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle, cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.ping.channel);
875 
876  for (rangeIdx = 0; rangeIdx < cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins; rangeIdx++)
877  {
878  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < cfg->staticCfg.numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
879  {
880  for (txAntIdx = 0; txAntIdx < cfg->staticCfg.numTxAntennas; txAntIdx++)
881  {
882  /* verify that previous DMA has completed */
883  startTimeWait = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
884  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_waitInData (obj, pingPongIdx);
885  waitingTime += Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTimeWait;
886 
887  /*Find index in radar cube for next EDMA.
888  Order from bringing data from radar cube is:
889  1. Next TX antennas for same range/RxAnt (to assure BPM can be decoded).
890  2. Next virtual antenna(which means next RxAnt for same TxAnt)
891  for same range (to assure sum of all virtual antennas can be computed).
892  3. Next range.
893  */
894  nextTransferTxIdx = txAntIdx + 1;
895  nextTransferRxIdx = rxAntIdx;
896  nextTransferRangeIdx = rangeIdx;
897 
898  if(nextTransferTxIdx == cfg->staticCfg.numTxAntennas)
899  {
900  nextTransferTxIdx = 0;
901  nextTransferRxIdx++;
902  if(nextTransferRxIdx == cfg->staticCfg.numRxAntennas)
903  {
904  nextTransferRxIdx = 0;
905  nextTransferRangeIdx++;
906  }
907  }
908 
909  nextTransferIdx = (nextTransferTxIdx * cfg->staticCfg.numRxAntennas * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps +
910  nextTransferRxIdx) * cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins + nextTransferRangeIdx;
911 
912  /*Last computation happens when nextTransferRangeIdx reaches numRangeBins.
913  This indicates that, the current virtual antenna is the last one for (numRangeBins-1).
914  Therefore, do not trigger next EDMA.*/
915  if(nextTransferRangeIdx < cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins)
916  {
917  /* kick off next DMA */
918  if (pingPongIdx == DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_PONG_IDX)
919  {
920  channel = cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.ping.channel;
921  }
922  else
923  {
924  channel = cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaIn.pong.channel;
925  }
926 
927  retVal = EDMA_setSourceAddress(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle, channel,
928  (uint32_t) &radarCubeBase[nextTransferIdx]);
929  if (retVal != 0)
930  {
931  goto exit;
932  }
933 
934  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle, channel);
935  }
936 
937  inpDoppFftBuf = (cmplx16ImRe_t *) &cfg->hwRes.pingPongBuf[pingPongIdx * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps];
938 
939  /* Remove static clutter? */
940  if (cfg->dynCfg.staticClutterCfg.isEnabled)
941  {
942  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_clutterRemoval(cfg, inpDoppFftBuf);
943  }
944 
945  /* The windowing output buffer is the input buffer for the Doppler FFT.
946  It needs to be padded with zeroes if number of Doppler chirps is less than
947  the number of Doppler bins.*/
948  if(cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins > cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps)
949  {
950  windowingOutBuf = (cmplx32ReIm_t*)cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf;
951  memset((void*)(&windowingOutBuf[cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps]), 0,
952  (cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins - cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps) * sizeof(cmplx32ReIm_t));
953  }
954 
955  /*Up to this point samples are in ImRe format, which is the radar cube format.
956  The windowing function will do IQ swap and the Doppler FFT is computed in
957  ReIm format.*/
958  mmwavelib_windowing16x32_IQswap((int16_t *) inpDoppFftBuf,
959  cfg->hwRes.windowCoeff,
960  (int32_t *) cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf,
961  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps);
962 
963  /*From this point forward samples are in ReIm format. In particular, FFT, twiddle are all in ReIm format.*/
964 
965  if(cfg->staticCfg.isBpmEnabled)
966  {
967  /*If BPM is enabled, the FFT output buffer stores 2 sets of
968  doppler bins so that BPM decoding can be done later on.*/
969  fftOutPtr = (int32_t *)&cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf[pingPongIdx * cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins];
970  }
971  else
972  {
973  /*If BPM is not enabled, the FFT output buffer stores 1 set of
974  doppler bins.*/
975  fftOutPtr = (int32_t *)&cfg->hwRes.fftOutBuf[0];
976  }
977 
978  /*DSPLIB notes for DSP_fft32x32():
979  Minimum FFT size is 16. Size must be power of 2.
980  No scaling done in FFT computation.*/
981  DSP_fft32x32((int32_t *)cfg->hwRes.twiddle32x32,
982  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins,
983  (int32_t *)cfg->hwRes.windowingLog2AbsBuf,
984  fftOutPtr);
985 
986  if(cfg->staticCfg.isBpmEnabled)
987  {
988  /*BPM is enabled.
989  Need both Ping and Pong to do the BPM decoding and then
990  do logAbsSum for the content of both buffers.*/
991  if (pingPongIdx == DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_PONG_IDX)
992  {
993  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_decode2TxBPM(obj, cfg);
994 
995  /*compute log2Abs and accumulate for PING*/
996  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_log2AbsAccum(obj, rxAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer,
997  txAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer, rangeIdx, &waitingTime, 0);
998 
999  /*compute log2Abs and accumulate for PONG*/
1000  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_log2AbsAccum(obj, rxAntIdx, txAntIdx, rangeIdx, &waitingTime,
1001  cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerBins);
1002  }
1003  else
1004  {
1005  /*Record previous indexes to be used later when both ping and pong are available
1006  for BPM decoding.*/
1007  rxAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer = rxAntIdx;
1008  txAntIdxBPMPreviousBuffer = txAntIdx;
1009  }
1010  }
1011  else
1012  {
1013  /*Not BPM*/
1014  /*Compute log2Abs and accumulate*/
1015  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_log2AbsAccum(obj, rxAntIdx, txAntIdx, rangeIdx, &waitingTime, 0);
1016  }
1017 
1018  pingPongIdx ^= 1;
1019  }/*txAntIdx*/
1020  } /* rxAntIdx */
1021 
1022  /* populate the detection matrix */
1023  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle, cfg->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaOut.channel);
1024  } /* for loop rangeIdx 0 to cfg->staticCfg.numRangeBins */
1025 
1026  /*Wait for last transfer to detection matrix to complete*/
1027  startTimeWait = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
1028  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_waitTransDetMatrix (obj);
1029  waitingTime += Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTimeWait;
1030 
1031  /*Update stats*/
1032  outParams->stats.numProcess++;
1033  outParams->stats.processingTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime - waitingTime;
1034  outParams->stats.waitTime = waitingTime;
1035 
1036 exit:
1037  if (obj != NULL)
1038  {
1039  obj->inProgress = false;
1040  }
1041 
1042  return retVal;
1043 }
1044 
1063 int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_control
1064 (
1065  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Handle handle,
1066  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Cmd cmd,
1067  void* arg,
1068  uint32_t argSize
1069 )
1070 {
1071  int32_t retVal = 0;
1072  DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *obj;
1073 
1074  obj = (DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj *)handle;
1075 
1076  if (obj == NULL)
1077  {
1078  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1079  goto exit;
1080  }
1081 
1082  /* Check if control() is called during processing time */
1083  if(obj->inProgress == true)
1084  {
1085  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
1086  goto exit;
1087  }
1088 
1089  /* Control command handling */
1090  switch(cmd)
1091  {
1092  case DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Cmd_staticClutterCfg:
1093  {
1094  if((argSize != sizeof(DPU_DopplerProc_StaticClutterRemovalCfg)) ||
1095  (arg == NULL))
1096  {
1097  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1098  goto exit;
1099  }
1100  else
1101  {
1102  /* Update the static clutter configuration. Nothing else needs to be done
1103  as this flag is checked during DPU processing time to decide if static clutter
1104  removal should be done.*/
1105  memcpy((void *)&obj->cfg.dynCfg.staticClutterCfg, (void *)arg, argSize);
1106  }
1107  }
1108  break;
1109 
1110  default:
1111  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_ECMD;
1112  break;
1113  }
1114 
1115 exit:
1116  return (retVal);
1117 }

1133 int32_t DPU_DopplerProcDSP_deinit(DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Handle handle)
1134 {
1135  int32_t retVal = 0;
1136 
1137  /* Free memory */
1138  if(handle == NULL)
1139  {
1140  retVal = DPU_DOPPLERPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1141  }
1142  else
1143  {
1144  MemoryP_ctrlFree(handle, sizeof(DPU_DopplerProcDSP_Obj));
1145  }
1146 
1147  return retVal;
